{{Short description|Pair of Shinto Shrines in Yamaguchi}}
{{Draft topics|east-asia}}
{{AfC topic|geo}}
{{AfC submission|||ts=20230407215208|u=Immanuelle|ns=118}}
{{draft}}
[[File:140720 Noda-jinja Yamaguchi Japan01s3.jpg|thumb|Entrance to the compound on which both are located]]
{{ill|Toyosaka and Noda Shrines|ja|豊榮神社・野田神社}} are a pair of adjacent [[Shinto shrine]]s located in [[Yamaguchi (city)|Yamaguchi]].<ref name=":0" /> Both shrines are dedicated to members of the [[Mōri clan]]

==Toyosaka Shrine==
{{Infobox Shinto shrine
| name                  = Toyosaka Shrine
| religious_affiliation = Shinto
| image                 = 140720 Toyosaka-jinja Yamaguchi Japan02s3.jpg
| deity                 = [[Mōri Motonari]]
| consecration_year     = 1762
}}


[[File:Mori_Motonari3.jpg|right|thumb|Full portrait of Motonari.]]
{{ill|Toyosaka Shrine|ja|豊榮神社・野田神社}} is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in [[Yamaguchi (city)|Yamaguchi]], it is located next to {{ill|Noda Shrine|ja|豊榮神社・野田神社}}<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Yamaguchi City Tourism Information Website Nishinokyo Yamaguchi - A strategic base of the Meiji Restoration. - Noda Shrine |url=https://yamaguchi-city.jp/w/en/ishin/spot018.html |access-date=2023-04-07 |website=yamaguchi-city.jp}}</ref>. It is dedicated to [[Mōri Motonari]]<ref>{{Cite web |title=Yamaguchi City Tourist Information {{!}} Toyosaka-jinjya Shinto Shrine {{!}}30{{!}} |url=https://yamaguchi-city.jp/signqr/details/en/30.html |access-date=2023-04-07 |website=yamaguchi-city.jp}}</ref>

==Noda Shrine==
{{ill|Noda Shrine|ja|豊榮神社・野田神社}} is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in [[Yamaguchi (city)|Yamaguchi]], it is located next to {{ill|Toyosaka Shrine|ja|豊榮神社・野田神社}}<ref name=":0" />. It is dedicated to [[Mōri Takachika|Mori Takachika]] and his son Mōri Motonori.<ref>{{Cite web |title=YAMAGUCHI JAPAN TRAVEL GUIDE |url=https://www.visit-jy.com/ |access-date=2023-04-07 |website=www.visit-jy.com}}</ref> 

{{Infobox Shinto shrine
| name                  = Noda Shrine
| religious_affiliation = Shinto
| image                 = 140720 Noda-jinja Yamaguchi Japan02s3.jpg
| deity                 = [[Mori Takachika]]
Mōri Motonori
| consecration_year     = 1873
}}

